LINEAR & BINARY SEARCH PROGRAM – SHORT IMPORTANT EXPLANATION

• account_ids:
  A list containing customer account ID numbers.

--------------------------------------
1) linear_search(account_list, target_id)
--------------------------------------
• Uses a simple loop to check each element one by one.
• enumerate() gives both index and value.
• If the value matches the target, return the index.
• If not found, return -1.
• Time Complexity: O(n)
• Space Complexity: O(1)

--------------------------------------
2) binary_search(account_list, target_id)
--------------------------------------
• Requires the list to be sorted.
• Uses low, high, and mid pointers.
• mid = (low + high) // 2 → integer division.
• If mid element is target → return index.
• If target > mid element → search right half.
• If target < mid element → search left half.
• If not found, return -1.
• Time Complexity: O(log n)
• Space Complexity: O(1)

--------------------------------------
3) sorted_ids = sorted(account_ids)
--------------------------------------
• sorted() is a built-in function.
• Returns a new sorted list; original list remains unchanged.
• Required because binary search only works on sorted lists.

--------------------------------------
4) Searching
--------------------------------------
• First perform Linear Search on original list.
• Then perform Binary Search on the sorted list.
• Based on result (index ≠ -1), print “Found” or “Not Found”.

--------------------------------------
5) Differences between Linear and Binary Search
--------------------------------------
• Linear Search:
    - Works on unsorted list.
    - Slow for large lists (O(n)).

• Binary Search:
    - Works only on sorted list.
    - Much faster (O(log n)).

--------------------------------------
6) -1 Meaning
--------------------------------------
• Returning -1 means the element is not present in the list.

--------------------------------------
7) Important Keywords
--------------------------------------
• enumerate() → gives index and value together.
• // → floor division (returns whole number index).
• len() → returns list length.
• sorted() → built-in function to sort list.
• return → exits function and sends result back.

--------------------------------------
8) Program Purpose
--------------------------------------
• To search for a customer account ID using both linear and binary search
  and display the result.
